{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638990","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638990"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:01:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:01:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17750"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17750"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.82,0.18,0,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10464"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74909"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10464","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10464"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17750"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60407"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2770"},{"type":"tags","id":"2840"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"},{"type":"tags","id":"9511"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24428"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24430"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74909","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74909"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with joint pain and stiffness in her hands that has been worsening over the past six months. She has morning stiffness lasting over an hour, improving with exercise. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her hands show swelling and tenderness in the proximal interphalangeal joints, and there is a noticeable deformity where the middle joint of the finger is bent downwards while the fingertip is bent upwards.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following types of arthritis is most likely to cause this deformity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Rheumatoid arthritis","Osteoarthritis","Psoriatic arthritis","Gout","Reactive arthritis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe deformity described in the stem is a \u003Cstrong\u003EBoutonni\u00e8re deformity\u003C/strong\u003E, which is characterised by flexion of the proximal interphalangeal joint and hyperextension of the distal interphalangeal joint. This deformity is most commonly associated with \u003Cstrong\u003Erheumatoid arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E, an autoimmune condition that leads to chronic inflammation of the joints and can result in various joint deformities if not adequately managed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoarthritis\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes joint pain and stiffness but is more commonly associated with Heberden\u0027s and Bouchard\u0027s nodes rather than Boutonni\u00e8re deformity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsoriatic arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E can cause joint deformities, but the classic deformity associated with it is the \u0027pencil-in-cup\u0027 deformity seen on X-ray, not Boutonni\u00e8re deformity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGout\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by acute episodes of joint inflammation due to uric acid crystal deposition, usually affecting the big toe, and does not cause a Boutonni\u00e8re deformity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReactive arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E is a post-infectious arthritis that can cause joint pain and swelling but is not associated with Boutonni\u00e8re deformity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Boutonni\u00e8re deformity is commonly associated with rheumatoid arthritis.","Rheumatoid arthritis is an autoimmune condition that primarily affects the joints, leading to deformities.","Early diagnosis and treatment of rheumatoid arthritis can prevent joint damage and deformities."],"references":["Binstead JT, Tafti D, Hatcher JD. Boutonniere Deformity. 2023 Aug 7. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29262145.","Khoo LS, Senna-Fernandes V. Revisiting the Curtis Procedure for Boutonniere Deformity Correction. World J Plast Surg. 2015 Jul;4(2):180-4. PMID: 26284190; PMCID: PMC4537613.","Harb A, Shawwa K, Alraiyes AH, Alraies MC. Severe rheumatoid arthritis hand deformity. BMJ Case Rep. 2013 May 2;2013:bcr2013009884. doi: 10.1136/bcr-2013-009884. PMID: 23645662; PMCID: PMC3670022.","Chetta M, Burns PB, Kim HM, Burke FD, Wilgis EFS, Fox DA, Chung KC. The effect of swan neck and boutonniere deformities on the outcome of silicone metacarpophalangeal joint arthroplasty in rheumatoid arthritis. Plast Reconstr Surg. 2013 Sep;132(3):597-603. doi: 10.1097/PRS.0b013e31829ad1c1. PMID: 23985634; PMCID: PMC4153347."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60407"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17750"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60407","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60407"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T09:52:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T09:53:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10464"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74909"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position